pull_request.title: CMake: Do not set march or mcpu when OQS_OPT_TARGET=generic
pull_request.body:
Currently, we try to pick a generic optimization target based on CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR when OQS_OPT_TARGET=generic. This is a bit tricky given the differences in available options in different versions of gcc and clang. For instance, -march=armv7-a works in gcc but not clang, so we pass -mcpu=cortex-a5 as a compromise.

This PR changes this behaviour, so now we will simply not set -march or -mcpu when OQS_OPT_TARGET=generic. It seems like gcc and clang currently set sensible defaults, but this may break in the future.

Resolves #1016.
